<item>
            <title>[CODEC-97] Base64 default constructor behaviour changed to enable chunking in 1.4</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-97</link>
                <project id="12310464" key="CODEC">Commons Codec</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following test passes in commons-codec 1.3 but fails in 1.4:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void testObjectEncode() &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; Exception {
    Base64 b64 = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Base64();
    assertEquals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;SGVsbG8gV29ybGQ=&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;(b64.encode(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Hello World&quot;&lt;/span&gt;.getBytes())));
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Commons-codec 1.3 returns &quot;SGVsbG8gV29ybGQ=&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Commons-codec 1.4 returns &quot;SGVsbG8gV29ybGQ=\r\n&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d understand if you want to close this as &quot;Won&apos;t Fix&quot;, since the behaviour wasn&apos;t documented before (the constructor wasn&apos;t even present!) and now it is. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, there is still no test for this behaviour on trunk as far as I can tell, so it would be good to add one so it doesn&apos;t change again in the future. I&apos;ll attach a patch for Base64Test which you can apply on trunk which will do so.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
